20situation%20is%20to%20assess%20other%20people's%20decisions%20and%20shut%20them%20down%20if%20necessary.%20Note%20that%20a%20vetoer%20never%20says%20%26quot%3Byes%2C%26quot%3B%20only%20%26quot%3Bno.%26quot%3B%20That's%20it.%20That's%20their%20sole%20contribution%20to%20the%20mental%20labor%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20vetoers%20think%20this%20negative%20contribution%20is%20important.%20After%20all%2C%20someone%20has%20to%20keep%20dreamers'%20feet%20planted%20to%20the%20ground.%20Someone%20has%20to%20offer%20a%20dose%20of%20reality%20to%20the%20delusional.%20But%20the%20thing%20about%20the%20deluded%20dreamers%20is%20that%20they%20have%20vision.%20Maybe%20it's%20an%20unachievable%20vision%2C%20and%20they%20have%20overlooked%20a%20dozen%20holes%20in%20their%20grand%20plan%2C%20but%20they%20are%20bringing%20something%20to%20the%20table.%20Meanwhile%2C%20a%20vetoer%20only%20takes%20things%20off%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20husband%20is%20a%20vetoer.%20He%20isn't%20offering%20a%20single%20idea%20for%20making%20up%20the%20looming%20deficit%20in%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbudgeting%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebudget%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20fact%2C%20from%20your%20letter%2C%20it%20seems%20he%20isn't%20worried%20about%20supplementing%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-social-security%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20all%2C%20because%20you%20will%20make%20the%20money%20work%20like%20you've%20always%20done%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20like%20that.%20Not%20in%20a%20way%20that%20means%20chopping%20up%20your%20home%20into%20rentable%20apartments.%20That%20might%20be%20inconvenient%20and%20uncomfortable%20for%20him.%20And%20he%20has%20a%20point%20%E2%80%94%20dividing%20up%20your%20home%20and%20inviting%20strangers%20in%20is%20a%20huge%20decision%20that%20will%20significantly%20alter%20nearly%20every%20facet%20of%20your%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20husband%20isn't%20fully%20onboard%20with%20the%20idea%2C%20then%20it's%20a%20no-go.%20This%20is%20not%20a%20question%20of%20compromise%3B%20either%20you%20both%20completely%20buy%20in%2C%20or%20you%20can't%20do%20it.%20Renting%20out%20a%20portion%20of%20your%20home%20is%20far%20from%20being%20a%20source%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-ways-to-earn-passive-income%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassive%20income%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20the%20other%20responsible%20adult%20in%20your%20marriage%2C%20your%20husband%20is%20obligated%20to%20offer%20an%20alternative.%20If%20he%20doesn't%2C%20the%20unspoken%20demand%20is%20clear%3A%20%26quot%3BFigure%20out%20our%20finances%2C%20honey%2C%20because%20I%20don't%20want%20to.%20Oh%2C%20and%20by%20the%20way%2C%20read%20my%20mind%20so%20you%20can%20anticipate%20which%20plans%20I%20will%20and%20won't%20approve.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20attitude%20is%20unfair%20and%20irresponsible.%20The%20person%20doing%20all%20the%20work%20should%2C%20by%20right%2C%20also%20get%20all%20the%20authority.%20But%20even%20that%20dynamic%20is%20far%20from%20the%20ideal.%20You%20two%20share%20a%20life%3B%20this%20means%20your%20life%20should%20also%20be%20a%20shared%20burden.%20But%20it's%20a%20burden%20that%20you%20are%20carrying%20alone%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20a%20human%20being%20with%20human%20limitations.%20You%20simply%20don't%20have%20all%20the%20skills.%20None%20of%20us%20do.%20This%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20benefit%20of%20marriage%20%E2%80%94%20pooling%20your%20talents%20with%20one%20another%2C%20counterbalancing%20one%20another's%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses%2C%20and%20ultimately%20optimizing%20your%20ability%20to%20carry%20the%20burden%20of%20life%20as%20a%20couple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20can%20continue%20preaching%20to%20the%20choir%20al