C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayover%20to%20Tucson%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20looked%20unimpressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe'd%20been%20waiting%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half%20when%20Eloise%20started%20screaming.%20I%20picked%20her%20up%20and%20bounced.%20She%20screeched.%20People%20stared.%20Five%20minutes%20passed.%20A%20grandmotherly%20agent%20finally%20took%20pity%20and%20escorted%20us%20to%20the%20front%20of%20the%20line.%20That%20was%20when%20Mochi%20peed%20on%20the%20airport%20floor%20(and%2C%20as%20we%20sprinted%20to%20the%20gate%2C%20pooped).%20We%20missed%20our%20connecting%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThanks%20to%20COVID%2C%2018%20months%20passed%20between%20that%20first%20Tucson%20trip%20and%20our%20next%20visit.%20Until%20then%2C%20Skype%20mercifully%20allowed%20my%20parents%20to%20see%20their%20granddaughter%20every%20week.%20But%20you%20can't%20hold%20and%20kiss%2C%20tickle%2C%20and%20chase%20over%20broadband.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20Thibault%20arrived%2C%20I%20couldn't%20justify%20a%2024-hour%20journey%20with%20two%20tiny%20humans.%20I%20always%20pitied%20the%20parent%20following%20a%20toddler%20up%20and%20down%20the%20airplane%20aisle%2C%20rocking%20a%20screaming%20baby.%20I%20had%20no%20appreciation%20of%20what%20it%20was%20like%20to%20be%20that%20parent%20until%20I%20became%20one%20myself.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20waited%20until%20the%20kids%20were%2018%20months%20and%204%20years%20old%20to%20venture%20back%20to%20my%20parents'%20house.%20The%20flight%2C%20combined%20with%20a%20nine-hour%20time%20change%2C%20was%20brutal.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20%E2%80%94%20usually%20relatively%20collaborative%20%E2%80%94%20fought%20nonstop.%20In%20over%20a%20year%2C%20we%20haven't%20been%20back.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22adcc5b09-46fc-416c-b1cc-88b401abbe1f%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20are%20getting%20older%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20upside%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww