-cut-13280307%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Ffinland-boards-russian-linked-oil-tanker-after-undersea-power-and-internet-cables-cut-13280307%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Ffinland-boards-russian-linked-oil-tanker-after-undersea-power-and-internet-cables-cut-13280307%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Apple%20exec%20lists%203%20reasons%20the%20iPhone%20maker%20doesn't%20want%20to%20build%20a%20search%20engine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20an%20iPhone%20with%20Google%20open%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653ad81e356802a56be565cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22681%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EApple%20has%20a%20multibillion-dollar%20deal%20with%20Google%20that%20makes%20Google%20the%20default%20search%20engine%20in%20Safari.%3Cp%3EJaap%20Arriens%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EApple%20exec%20Eddy%20Cue%20explained%20why%20the%20company%20has%20not%20built%20its%20own%20search%20engine.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle%20has%20a%20deal%20with%20Apple%20to%20be%20its%20default%20search%20engine%2C%20and%20Apple%20wants%20to%20keep%20it%20that%20way.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20exec%20explained%20Apple's%20reasoning%20in%20a%20filing%20related%20to%20the%20DOJ's%20antitrust%20case%20against%20Google.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20says%20it%20plans%20to%20stick%20to%20what%20it%20knows%20best%2C%20and%20that%20doesn't%20include%20building%20its%20own%20search%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20court%20papers%20filed%20this%20week%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20Eddy%20Cue%2C%20Apple's%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20services%2C%20listed%20the%20reasons%20the%20iPhone%20maker%20does%20not%20want%20to%20create%20its%20own%20search%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20filing%20was%20made%20in%20connection%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-proposal-remedies-resolve-search-antitrust-case-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eantitrust%20case%20against%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20argues%20that%20Google%20has%20an%20illegal%20monopoly%20over%20the%20search%20engine%20market.%20One%20of%20the%20DOJ's%20key%20pieces%20of%20evidence%20in%20the%20trial%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-apple-iphone-search-engine-safari-deal-20-billion-2022-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevenue-sharing%20deal%20between%20Google%20and%20Apple%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20makes%20Google%20the%20default%20search%20engine%20on%20Apple's%20Safari%20browser%20on%20all%20its%20devices.%20Google%20has%20been%20paying%20Apple%20for%20this%20default%20search%20engine%20status%20since%202002.%20Google's%20payout%20has%20increased%20dramatically%20over%20the%20years%2C%20rising%20to%20around%20%2420%20billion%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20had%20asked%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20trial%20to%20defend%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-antitrust-apple-search-payments-iphone-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epartnership%20with%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Ftechnology%2Fapple-seeks-defend-googles-billion-dollar-payments-search-case-2024-12-24%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20And%20in%20this%20week's%20filing%2C%20Cue%20explained%20the%20motivation%20behind%20the%20deal%2C%20including%20why%20Apple%20uses%20Google's%20search%20engine%20instead%20of%20creating%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20gave%20three%20main%20reasons%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3EDeveloping%20a%20search%20engine%20would%20%26quot%3Bcost%20billions%20of%20dollars%20and%20take%20many%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Cue%20said%20in%20the%20filing.%20He%20added%20that%20it%20would%20divert%20employees%20and%20capital%20investment%20away%20from%20the%20company's%20other%20areas%20of%20growth.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESearch%20is%20%26quot%3Brapidly%20evolving%26quot%3B%20alongside%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20and%20investing%20in%20it%20now%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Beconomically%20risky%2C%26quot%3B%20Cue%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESearch%20engines%20require%20a%20platform%20to%20sell%20targeted%20advertising%2C%20and%20that%20is%20not%20a%20core%20part%20of%20Apple's%20business%2C%20Cue%20said.%20He%20said%20Apple%20also%20does%20not%20have%20the%20staff%20or%20operational%20infrastructure%20to%20build%20out%20a%20successful%20search%20advertising%20business.%20And%20he%20said%20it%20could%20conflict%20with%20Apple's%20%26quot%3Blongstanding%20privacy%20commitments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3ECue%20said%20the%20DOJ%20is%20wrongly%20assuming%20that%2C%20without%20a%20deal%20with%20Google%2C%20Apple%20would%20create%20its%20own%20search%20engine.%20Cue%20said%20that's%20not%20likely%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20case's%20outcome.%20And%20he%20warned%20that%20if%20the%20DOJ%20blocks%20Google's%20revenue-sharing%20deal%20with%20Apple%2C%20then%20%26quot%3Bit%20would%20hamstring%20Apple's%20ability%20to%20continue%20delivering%20products%20that%20best%20serve%20its%20users'%20needs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECue%20also%20highlighted%20Apple's%20revenue-sharing%20agreements%20with%20other%20search%20engines.%20These%20include%20deals%20that%20give%20Yahoo!%2C%20Microsoft%20Bing%2C%20DuckDuckGo%2C%20and%20Ecosia%20access%20to%20Apple%20users'%20Safari%20search%20queries%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20Apple%20considered%20buying%20Microsoft's%20Bing%20search%20engine%20or%20investing%20in%20a%20multibillion-dollar%20deal%20to%20allow%20Bing%20to%20supplement%20some%20of%20Google's%20dominance%20on%20Apple%20devices%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F10%2F05%2Fapple-considered-buying-bing-from-micros