ist%2C%20technocrat%20and%20the%20architect%20of%20India's%20liberalisation%2C%20which%20pulled%20the%20country%20out%20of%20economic%20atrophy%20-%20has%20died%20at%2092.%20Dr%20Singh%2C%20who%20had%20been%20ailing%20for%20a%20while%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flive-updates-manmohan-singh-hospitalised-at-aiims-family-reaches-hospital-7338179%5C%22%3Edied%20at%20Delhi's%20AIIMS%20hospital%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeen%20as%20a%20reluctant%20politician%2C%20Manmohan%20Singh%20was%20the%20automatic%20choice%20for%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20when%2C%20after%20an%20unexpected%20victory%20of%20the%20Congress-led%20UPA%2C%20she%20stepped%20away%20from%20the%20post%20of%20Prime%20Minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnational-mourning-for-7-days-to-honour-manmohan-singh-sources-7338892%23pfrom%3Dhome-ndtv_topscroll%5C%22%3EDr%20Singh's%20background%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%20Governor%20and%20former%20finance%20minister%2C%20and%20his%20unimpeachable%20reputation%20made%20it%20an%20obvious%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20economy%20has%20never%20looked%20back%20after%20the%20liberalisation%20of%201991%20that%20pulled%20it%20out%20of%20a%20phenomenal%20low%20of%20the%20balance%20of%20payments%20crisis%2C%20delivering%20an%20average%20growth%20rate%20of%20around%208.5%20per%20cent%2C%20Manmohan%20Singh%20took%20the%20other%20huge%20step%2C%20in%20foreign%20policy%2C%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20India-US%20nuclear%20deal%20was%20forged%20in%20the%20fire%20of%20a%20huge%20political%20row%20in%20the%20country%2C%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20support%20by%20the%20left%20Front%2C%20which%20left%20Dr%20Singh's%20government%20confronting%20a%20test%20of%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deal%20he%20stood%20by%20ended%20the%20era%20of%20sanctions%20placed%20on%20India%20after%20the%20Pokhran%202%20nuclear%20tests%20of%201998%2C%20with%20partial%20sanctions%20by%20IAEA%20that%20covered%20only%20the%20civil%20nuclear%20facilities.%20It%20also%20steered%20the%20country%20away%20from%20the%20Nehruvian%20policy%20of%20non-alignment%2C%20placed%20it%20front%20and%20centre%20of%20the%20international%20community%20and%20secured%20it%20a%20place%20at%20the%20nuclear%20club%20high%20table.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Singh's%20political%20journey%20of%20over%20three%20decades%20saw%20his%20meteoric%20rise%20from%20a%20post-partition%20humble%20background%20to%20the%20country's%20highest%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%20Gah%20in%20undivided%20Punjab%20(now%20in%20Pakistan)%20on%20September%2026%2C%201932%2C%20Dr%20Singh%20was%20a%20brilliant%20student%20who%20got%20a%20first%20class%20degree%20in%20Economics%20from%20Cambridge%20University%20and%20a%20DPhil%20from%20Oxford%20in%20the%20early%201960s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20handpicked%20as%20finance%20minister%20by%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20after%20having%20held%20almost%20every%20top%20job%20in%20the%20government%3A%20Chief%20Economic%20Advisor%2C%20Deputy%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Planning%20Commission%2C%20%C2%A0Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20Governor%20and%20Union%20Finance%20Secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Dr%20Singh's%20personal%20honesty%20was%20never%20questioned%2C%20his%20government%20faced%20allegations%20of%20corruption%20and%20%C2%A0policy%20paralysis%20in%20its%20final%20years.%20Allegations%20linked%20to%20the%202G%2C%20CWG%20and%20Coal%20block%20allocations%20were%20seized%20by%20the%20Opposition%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20huge%20criticism%20against%20his%20government%20was%20sparked%20by%20the%20perception%20of%20then%20party%20chief%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20as%20a%20parallel%20power%20centre.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20critics%20even%20disparagingly%20dubbed%20him%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BAccidental%20Prime%20Minister%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Singh%2C%20howeve